Pre-Game Insights: England and Pakistan are set to clash in a thrilling four-match T20I series in England, beginning on May 22.
England’s recent form in T20I matches has been a mixed bag with two wins and three losses in their last five games.
Pakistan’s recent T20I form shows a slightly more positive trend with three wins out of their last five matches.
England’s T20I captain, Jos Buttler, might miss some of the ENG vs. PAK series.
The pitch at Headingley, Leeds, is expected to be an average-pace bowling track with moderate assistance for fast bowlers and some assistance for spinners.
Weather conditions for the match are expected to be clear with a temperature of approximately 16.1°C and minimal cloud cover.
